LG Electronics East Africa has rolled out a campaign that enables customers to save up to 1.0m/- in the next five weeks when purchasing its various products. The products, according to press release, ranged from home entertainment, home appliance to residential air conditioners. The campaign that rolled out across the country aimed to improve customers’ shopping experience and relations with LG. The campaign, which will run until mid-next month, offers shoppers up to 20 per cent price reduction on selected products in addition to adding value and benefits for customers. The offers will run in LG branded shops, partner shops and supermarkets including shoppers and game super market. LG East Africa Managing Director Sa Nyoung Kim said the campaign main goal is to enable customers to have a more convenient life through the latest innovation of the products. “Our main goal is to comfort the customers to live a better, and more convenient life through our latest innovations and products,” said Mr Kim. He also added that Tanzanians have a great opportunity to replace and upgrade their home entertainment with new, modern technology and more efficient appliances. “This is also an opportunity for Tanzanians to replace and upgrade their home entertainment with new, modern technology and more efficient appliances that they have waited for a long time,” said Mr Kim.